      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, im working on a paper for my linguistics class about how people perceive different ways of speaking in professional jobs. can u help me look at these two snippets? i wanna know which one sounds more \"intellectual\" and \"capable\" for someone applying to be a professor at a top university.\n\nSnippet 1: \"The study explores the multifaceted implications of socioeconomic stratification on urban development, noting a significant correlation between density and resource allocation.\"\n\nSnippet 2: \"The way the city grew really shows how much money and stuff depends on where people live, like, the layout actually changes how the resources get distributed to different spots.\"\n\nwhich one would a hiring committee think is more competent?",
