    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i was wondering if the \"vibe\" of the language itself is tied to something more specific. like, if snippet 2 was written by someone using AAVE (African American Vernacular English) instead of just casual speech, would that change how a committee views their intelligence? does the dialect itself carry a stigma of being less academic or less \"serious\" in those high-level circles?",
